<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-657-360  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 657 360.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  July 20 1990 n1472* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Clayton andamp; Dubilier typewriter unit buyer for IBM. (leveragedbuyout firm attempting to acquire IBM keyboard, typewriter,low-end printer factory in Lexington, KY)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (acquisitions and mergers)Clayton and Dubilier Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     TypewritersAcquisitionLow Performance Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CLAYTON andamp; DUBILIER TYPEWRITER UNIT BUYER FOR IBMandM;The would-be acquirer of IBM's typewriter, low-end printer and keyboardbusinesses centred on the 4,000-employee Lexington, Kentucky factory, wasyesterday identified by the Wall Street Journal as leveraged buyoutpartnership Clayton andamp; Dubilier of New York.andP;  The company has already helpedfinance the buyout of low technology units of Harris Corp, and in the dealsthat it has set up so far, employee shareholders have typically taken about25% of the company.andP;  It also generally eschews the big sell-offs and sackingsthat have typically followed buy-outs so that it is in a position to reassureIBM on worries over employment protection.andP;  It has also said that it wants toparticipate in bigger buyouts than hitherto - above the $1,000m level.andP;  Wordon the Street is that the deal will be of the order of $2,500m to $3,000m,implying that some other IBM units will be included.andO;</TEXT></DOC>